OUR story
Hyatt was founded by Jay Pritzker in 1957 when he purchased the Hyatt House motel adjacent to the Los Angeles International Airport. Over the following decade, Jay Pritzker and his brother, Donald Pritzker, working together with other Pritzker family business interests, grew the company into a North American management and hotel ownership company, which became a public company in 1962. In 1968, Hyatt International was formed and subsequently became a separate public company. Hyatt Corporation and Hyatt International Corporation were taken private by the Pritzker family business interests in 1979 and 1982, respectively. On December 31, 2004, substantially all of the hospitality assets owned by Pritzker family business interests, including Hyatt Corporation and Hyatt International Corporation, were consolidated under a single entity, now Hyatt Hotels Corporation.
 
 
 
 
 
















1957




Jay Pritzker purchases the first Hyatt House, a small motor hotel adjacent to the Los Angeles International Airport, from business partner Hyatt von Dehn.
Hyatt was founded by a family. And we maintain the feeling of family among colleagues today - many of whom stay with us for decades and inspire their children to join us, too.










1967




Hyatt Regency Atlanta, Hyatt Hotels & Resorts' first Hyatt Regency and first major John C. Portman-designed hotel, opens in Atlanta, Georgia. Its dramatic, 22-story atrium lobby and groundbreaking design spawn many imitators and define Hyatt as a leading innovator in global hospitality.
We’ve always had an entrepreneurial, forward-thinking spirit to help lead us to innovations, like our signature open atrium.










1969




Hyatt Regency Hong Kong, Hyatt's first international hotel, opens its doors.










1972




A central reservations office with a toll-free 800 number opens in Omaha, Nebraska.
Every milestone marks our evolution of hospitality and dedication to care.










1980




Grand Hyatt New York and Park Hyatt Chicago become the newest members of Hyatt's brand portfolio.










1987




Hyatt Gold Passport global frequent guest program debuts.










1990s




Hyatt unveils the new tagline "Feel the Hyatt Touch" and the new Hyatt crescent logo. Each is meant to symbolize the Hyatt touch and "sunrise-to-sunset service." Hyatt's first online presence is launched. As a main driver of revenue, Hyatt.com has generated several billion dollars to date. Hyatt enters the vacation ownership industry in 1994, opening its first Vacation Club property, Hyatt Sunset Harbor, in Key West, Florida, the following year.










2005




Hyatt moves into the Pritzker Realty-developed Hyatt Center office tower in Chicago, Illinois.










2006




The Hyatt Place brand is introduced in Lombard, Illinois. Hyatt acquires Summerfield Suites—an extended suite stay—and renames it Hyatt Summerfield Suites.











2007




Andaz, currently our only brand without the Hyatt name, opens its debut location-Andaz Liverpool Street London.
We have the capabilities to be the fastest-growing multi-brand, multinational hotel company. When we find ideas that stick, we are able to implement them quickly on a global scale.










2009




The initial public offering of Class A common stock is completed. The stock begins trading publicly on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol H.










2011




Hyatt Thrive, Hyatt's global corporate responsibility platform, is introduced.
Environmental stewardship and community engagement have always been part of Hyatt's culture; with Hyatt Thrive we created a format that broadened our reach and impact.










2012




Hyatt Summerfield Suites is rebranded as Hyatt House. Fifteen Hotel Sierra properties are aquired and become part of the Hyatt House brand, further evolving our extended-stay experience.
We are in the hotel business, but our real business is taking care of people who happen to be staying at hotels.











2013




Hyatt enters the rapidly-growing, all-inclusive resort segment with the debut of the Hyatt Ziva and Hyatt Zilara brands in Mexico.
Ever since our founding moment, we've created brands that are based on caring for our guests' needs.










2015




In January, Hyatt announced the Hyatt Centric brand, a new lifestyle concept that delivers an upscale, cosmopolitan experience in the heart of prime destinations.








